The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 26 August is 2,922 (338.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 22 August, there were 52 new confirmed cases (6.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 15 August, there were 32 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 62% (20 extra cases).
